One set of cleaners came in to do the sheets and were surprised to see me, and another Spanish guy came in, as I was stood in my underwear,to clean. Unfortunately my Spanish wasn't good enough to explain that I had booked a late checkout, so I was awkwardly trying to get ready, as he cleaned around me. Review Title: Tolerable for a night or two but there are better hostels out there
Negative Reviews:
I stayed here for two nights in two different bookings (at the beginning and end of my trip), and both nights I was placed in a room in the basement whose only windows faced the smoking area. The room stank of cigarette smoke and there were drunk smokers outside the window shouting until past 3am, waking me up at all hours. They don't warn you about this when you check in. Thankfully I'm not super sensitive to cigarette smoke but anyone else who is should be warned. (I stayed in the 8-bed female dorm room both times).

The locker situation is not ideal. The only in-room storage provided are these tiny, under-bed drawers that are too shallow to fit any suitcase. Unless you are comfortable just leaving your suitcase in the room (as many of my roommates did) and locking anything valuable in the under-bed drawers, you're going to have to rent one of the lockers outside for a fee. 

Finally, my bed wasn't very clean at all when I arrived, and I saw several strands of hair and nail clippings around my mattress.
Positive Reviews: The staff were nice and helpful, despite clearly being understaffed. The location is also fantastic, close to St. Pancras and the tube and in a lovely neighbourhood, in walking distance to British Museum. The fan in my room kept it from being too stuffy. I also liked the bar being open quite late as it provided somewhere to get a quick bite to eat late at night without having to leave.

(I had originally planned to only stay 2 nights as I had accommodation booked elsewhere however the other place was not for me so I came back and booked whatever I could at late notice). 
The place is cleaned throughout the day my multiple staff members and the desk staff were always there to help when needed. 
The location between 2 underground stations (Kings Cross and Russell Square, made for easy transport links around the city), it was also in a location where if like me you enjoy walking then everywhere was walkable (I was clocking 30,000 steps a day). 
The private rooms were a great respite after a busy day and the bed was super comfortable. One private room I had was on the 5th floor was a lot quieter than the other one I had on the 2nd floor but this was mainly due to people being loud late at night in the hallway. 
The dorm rooms I experienced were both on the basement level (both a female only dorm and a mixed dorm) this was ok for the price point. I loved the added mirrors and bench top in the female dorm room to be able to get ready. 
The mixed dorm was an interesting experience and something I hadnâ€™t done in a long time.

Review Title: Pleasant but could use some air-con to combat global warming
Negative Reviews:
There was no air-conditioning or proper ventilation within the rooms. The windows were bolted in and you can only open them up to a certain degree and it barely allows any airflow. 

It was an oven because buildings in London are meant to keep heat in, and during the heatwave, temperatures soared to 35-37 degrees.

They provided fans but they are not exactly powerful enough to combat the heatwave, granted that it was not expected or taken into account but this is something to take note of when traveling during the summer period. 

The toilets were shared but they are in good condition.
Positive Reviews:
The location for this place was quite accessible and very central. Near the Russel Square Station tube and you can pretty much walk to King's Cross and Euston Station to travel around. 

Booked the 4-men bunk and the room was very small but still enough to have your own spaces. 

Cleanliness was expected of a hostel, nothing too stellar.

You can meet other like-minded travelers and make new friends in this setting without it feeling awkward. 

It is in a rather safe neighborhood with a supermarket just 3 minutes' walk away for your groceries or needs. 

Breakfast was very affordable with a good variety (9 pounds). 

Drinks in the bar were also very affordable and it gives you opportunities to make new friends.
Room Type: Bed in 4 Bed Dorm - Shared Bathrooms

Everything else. First of, the smell in the hallways was really bad and they could benefit from a good air circulation system and air conditioning. Our room smelled at least a bit less worse than the hallway, but was still very hot.
The bed was so close to the ceiling, you just would hit your head no matter what. Some soft padding on the ceiling and a warning would be greatly appreciated. The bed was uncomfortable and lumpy. We missed pillow cases to make up the bed, went to the reception and got 2, but 1 of them was still dirty. 
I didn't even dare to take a shower with the look of those facilities. Also, only 2 toilets for the whole floor is not enough. 
A map of the floor and where you can find the nearest toilet/shower would also be great. 
The music from the common area's was so loud, we couldn't sleep. Also, all the other doors on the floor opening and closing made so much noise you could wake the dead. There was also the sound of the sewers so close to my head when I lay in bed, I was afraid it would all come down on me. Think things couldn't get any worse? We were woken by the fire alarm! Luckily, it was nothing serious and was turned off after some minutes, but there was no mention of everything being okay or something. Also, no one seemed to have taking this alarm seriously, given the state of other occupants, which is going to be a problem if they do have a real emergency. 
Really, this was way too much money for a really bad experience. I would definitely advice people to stay away from this place if you can afford something else.

The showers are terrible. Many were out of order. When you try to have a shower water goes everywhere, soaking the floor and the adjacent showers. There's no room to get changed, dry off or hang up your stuff. The experience of having a shower is really uncomfortable.

The bar area and adjacent room are full of shuffleboards that take up space. Hardly anyone uses them. It means that part of the bar area is always out of use, and the room where breakfast is served is really cramped. The hostel should stop its obsession with these huge shuffleboards and get rid of some of them to allow for more comfortable seating.

Sometimes the bar music is really loud, which means there's nowhere to just chill out, do some work or enjoy a quiet coffee. This is particularly the case at weekends when the music in the bar can be overly loud and obnoxious.

Review Title: Great location, sadly disappointing room and visit compared to previous stay.

For this visit I was in a room directly under the bar area which had music playing through the ceiling until 3am most nights and 4am on Saturday. Understand and appreciate this is a youth hostel, and I enjoyed the bar when there, but it's unacceptable how loud the music is in the rooms below. Completely unable to sleep when the bar was open which meant most nights I only got a couple of hours. Strongly recommend avoiding any dorms around 014 - you'll be directly beneath the bar. Either that or bring ear defenders.

Negative Reviews:
the shower rooms have absolutely no spot for you to leave your belongings or clothing your wearing while your taking a shower, there's hooks scattered around but they really need a box in the shower stall, a shelf in the shower stall, best case scenario maybe lockers.  SOMETHING.  

on our last day i tried to use the sink for the first time, as i was using the sinks in the shower room for the rest of my stay, and it would not shut off.  it flooded the sink flooded the room, and got water all over our things.  i ran down to the "24 hour front desk" and there was no one there, i grabbed the first person i found that looked like an employee and they were really annoyed that i interrupted them to tell them the sink was flooding and that our room was flooding, it took about 10 min to get someone to the room by then we got it slowed down to a slow drip but there was a large puddle all over the floor,  he turned the sink off for us and told us the faucet was faulty and it would need to be replaced. this was our check out day so i have no clue if they really did exchange it out.  if your in room 215 be weary of the faucet!
Positive Reviews: Location was great, right near Kings Cross station and then another stop on the Piccadilly line.  easy to get to anything you want to do via train.  we had a private room w/ bunk bed, it had a sink in it, a desk and a bench good size for what we paid for. bed was comfy enough to sleep on im not to picky about bed.  they have a bar downstairs, they offer breakfast in the morning, and at night they have an area for a night club, one of the nights we were there, they did karaoke, they also have shuffleboard you can book to do.

Review Title: Good stay, the location is great, but i had an unpleasant experience.
Negative Reviews:
1) None of the staffs bothered to help me out when i reached out to them. When i checked out, that evening i came to collect my luggages, I really needed a charger as my phone battery was almost zero. they told me i had to purchase the connector plug for 8 pounds which i clearly didnt want to do as it was my last day. But common guys, i was checked out and was asking them for at least a few minutes to charge.... they saw me struggling with it and yet nobody really cared. 
One lady rudely told me that she cant help. And because of this i had to reach the airport with my phone switched off and had to face a lot of issues. Please be kind to the travelers as they come here from different countries and not all know about the changes in the systems or carry the appropriate things at that time. ( i didnt know the connector plug for the sockets. )Had a very sad ending at this hostel when i checked out due to this incident. 

2) They charge extra to keep our luggage after check out. The check out time is 10am. But my flight was at 9:00pm and i had to leave my luggage at the locker for which i had to pay 6 pounds for 6 hours. 

3) The washroom showers in 5th floor where i stayed was not operational and i had to go to the fourth floor for showers. The shower cubicles are vvvvveeerrrryyyyy small. Like you cant even hang ur towel n clothes. 

4) The toilets in fourth floor was veeery dirty. all of them were either clogged or had some unpleasant sights left behind by the previous user. The fifth floor mens washroom had only two toilets and it was dirty too. Felt really uncomfortable.
but a couple of times it was cleaned though . 

5) The rooms are extremely small. I stayed in a 4 bed room and theres place only for one person to stand in the middle and if he opens his luggage , it occupies all the space.
Positive Reviews:
The bed was comfortable.  The location is great. Made some good friends. 
Overall the location is the plus point.

Another dissadvantage is that near some of beds are not sockets that is inconvienient.
 There is light instaled above head but it is not working.

Negative Reviews:
rooms were very small and although the atmosphere was great in comparison to other generators the facilities were lacking here, the room I was in was so tight my suitcase could barely get in the door around the beds into the main part of the room which isnâ€™t ideal especially when arriving late and trying not to disturb other guests, and really only one person at a time in my 6 bed dorm were able to open bags and re arrange or get stuff out of suitcases on floor and get stuff from the lockers under bed.
i had had a long day of travel delays and had to wait around half an hour at 1am to check in as there was so many people at front desk trying to get last minute accommodations, which I understand given the weekend I was here however it would be more efficient if one out of four staff could atleast serve people with bookings especially that late at night itâ€™s frustrating having to wait for people with no original bookings as takes so long, to top it off my key didnâ€™t work 2 times so I had to leave my suitcase in the hall and lug my duffle bag with valuables back up and down everytime, and then my phone was almost flat and they only have usb chargers on the bed- better than nothing but most modern iPhones no longer have usb and every other generator Iâ€™ve stayed at had a proper power outlet on the bed so that was extremely frustrating I would have too go down and sit in cafe every morning for half an hour to an hour and charge phone before I could go out for the day, it didnâ€™t appear there was any wall chargers near my bed either but I donâ€™t feel comfortable leaving my phone charging anywhere other than in the bed anyways.
bathrooms were ok but definitely felt a bit grungy could do with good deep clean and upgrades, the showers on level 5 wouldnâ€™t drain so you would stand in ankle deep water getting in and out, Iâ€™m pretty short and my head was close to roof and shower head so probably not ideal for tall people as well.
Positive Reviews:
good location close by to kings cross station which runs later than the other line at Russell square so just something to keep in mind if out late, Russell square line will take you straight to Heathrow so really liked that, I would just walk the 30-40mins into the main part of London along the river. 
seems to be a safe enough area and quite quiet. 
great atmosphere, Iâ€™ve stayed at a few generator hostels now and probably helped I was here on a busy weekend but was cool to see the bar alive and a good social atmosphere as bars at other ones Iâ€™ve stayed at were closed and it was always very quiet around, was pumping and was on level 6 and never heard a thing once I got in the lift.

seemed to be security on door at nights which is appreciated

Review Title: Great stay but let down by IT check-in/check-out gremlins
Negative Reviews: Experienced a few IT gremlins - I booked a 4 bed private dorm but the self check-in system would only activate 1 keycard, we needed 4, so I had to queue at reception to talk to a human (it was very busy at 2pm). Self check-in also said my checkout time was 10am despite paying for a late check-out, so I had to also check that with reception. Then in the morning I went for a shower and couldn't get back into the room as the keycard wouldn't work - it was after 10am so I guess the system automatically disabled our cards, even though once again I had paid for a late check-out. I was stood there not wearing very much with all my belongings locked in the room, I was about to go down 5 floors in not much more than my underwear to reception when I managed to wake one of my roommates who opened the door. So it just feels like the whole check-in/check-out process was beset with IT gremlins. Also there is only 1 lift for the whole building and it takes ages to call, we ended up using the stairs (up/down 5 floors!). Finally, there was no shelf in the shower so I had nowhere to put my wash bag, ended up wedging it in the gap between the ceiling and cubicle.

The coffee was nice at the bar. The room is very small. I stayed in a mixed dorm of 4 people. There was no space to keep any suitcase and its narrow enough to just walk through and get into your bed. Thankfully I rented the locker on ground floor. It was warm in the room and the windows cannot be open fully. There are nearby shops, cafes and take away food so this is fine as they are open until 10pm. Also the park is nearby. Its just ok to sleep and nothing more. Review Title: If you need a bed? Book elsewhere
Negative Reviews:
Having stayed at the Generator Hostels around Europe Amsterdam, Berlin, Paris have been amazing, however the big one London is I would say the worst hostel I have stayed in. The fact that I was allocated a bed and someone else was sleeping in it. Not only this as a hostel manager myself,  the guests said the company made a mistake. 3 people 4 beds.. hardly a mistake. I believe that bed hopping happens alot here and it is not the first time. I had no pillow no staff to be found so ended up paying for a 4 bed room wil no pillow no cover. However I just got off a 14 hour flight and just slept in what appeared to be a moved bed. 

Staff should be more robust. And also stop other people sleeping in other allocated beds.

Spoke to the staff and they just said sorry.

Â£24 I know what a hostel is all about, but a hostel is not just about sleeping, it is to feel a home from home, but i will be staying at another hostels instead such as st Christopher's or YCA. Generator has really let me down this time.

Review Title: Really disappointing as room wasn't ready, despite having an early check-in confirmed.
Negative Reviews:
Our room wasn't ready despite getting confirmation for an early check-in for a hen party. 

I arrived at 12.15pm with two other people in our party as I had sorted an early check-in. The woman behind the desk was apologetic but explained that the confirmation I had received from Generator London via Booking.com was sent in error (by someone who did not know the system) and that early check-ins are not available. She also emphasised that it was a Saturday and particularly busy today. This was incredibly frustrating as we had lots of bags and requested an early check-in so that we could decorate the dorm room for a Hen do, before a local drinks booking we had at 3pm. I explained that this was why we had requested (and had confirmed) and early check-in, which stated we could have the room between 12-1pm. This was really disappointing as we had no time to get ready or decorate the room, before our other friends (including the bride) got there. It was all a big rush and there was nothing that could be done for us except to wait somewhere until our room was ready (with all our things and decorations). The woman on the desk did try and speed up the cleaning of the room for us, however, we were still rushed and only had 45 mins (for 6 girls) to meet and get ready. 

To make it worse, while we were waiting for the room, I went to use the ladies toilets in the lobby but they were closed for cleaning and the cleaner did not know where other ones were. I went back to the desk and was advised where there were more (downstairs and round a corner). 

When we came back that night (around 11pm), we were sure to be quiet as the signs around the building outside said, however did not sleep well due to outside party noise inside and outside (within the hostel). We also woke up with bad backs due to the beds being uncomfortable! We had each stayed in hostels before and were prepared for a value-for-money experience but did not find this enjoyable at all.

Also, if you're looking for a place to sleep, which a hostel is for, do not come to the Generator Hostel in London. Here there was continuous loud shouting from drunks in the smoking area of the 24/7 bar, which was right next to the room window. You can also hear and feel the underground every few minutes. The staff did nothing when asked. In addition, there were some snorers in the room, but it was not the hostel's fault. The rooms and bathrooms were mostly clean. It was still an absolute horror. And for that I booked 85 euros per night in a 10-bed dormitory because of the short notice. On top of that, there were extra fees for luggage storage and there is no kitchen, so even allergy sufferers would be forced to buy food there (not possible in my case). Therefore: NEVER AGAIN!

Clearly the worst hostel I went to so far. I know that London is not especially known for the hostels, but still a bad experience.

First the hostel is clearly more a hotel than a "youth hostel". Full of families, and mostly people in their 40, 50. And these people we clearly not backpackers.
So it was quite impossible to meet other travelers in the hostel.

Secondly many people seem to live in the hostel, there was semone in my room whose locker was full of food. Also there was a Deliveroo bag on a shelf. Someone even took control of the only sink in the room, making it really hard for the other to access it.
So clearly not what a hostel should look like.

Third, there is no kitchen, regarding the prices of the food at the bar and the price of the room, it is clearly not acceptable.

Fourth, the place is clearly not comfortable. Only found 4 showers in my whole floor. And god, these were the worse shower I saw in a hostel... No space to hang your clothes, just enough for you towel (don't even think about your toiletry bag...) not even a place to put your soap on... And the shower itself is like 30 cm away from the hook where you put you towel, which end soaked. So few space that a guy finaly managed to leave the shower full naked and put his clothes on outside of the shower. Even the sink got no space to put you toiletry bag. And of course the place look dirty and it smells like sewers.

Fifth, half of the toilets lockers or door were broken and toilet paper in just one of them during my 3 days stay... Cleaning woman will get mad at you if you are in the toilet while they are cleaning.

Sixth, 8Â£ for a 24h locker, seriously ? Most of the hostel I went to it was free of charge and when I had to pay it was never more than 3â‚¬. And I wont speak about paid earplugs...

Review Title: Generator far exceeded our "hostel"  expectations. Loved it!
Negative Reviews: Smoking area should be on every floor! ðŸ˜€ðŸ˜€ðŸ˜€
Positive Reviews:
As a 60 year old  lifetime traveller who until now have had  stayed only in hotels, from 2* hotels in southern Cuba,  to 5* Marriott in Montreal and Shangri-la in Hong Kong, this time visiting London on coronation weekend visit I finally made one of my long time dreams come true: To stay at hostel for few nights.

My wife was first  hesitant when we booked however upon arrival we were both surprised how comfy, clean and safe this place was.

For our use we had reserved 2 lower  beds in a small room about 3x3m, with two bunkies.  Solid steel,  metal-framed beds that did not squeak at all ðŸ˜‰

During check-in I asked receptionist to let just two of us stay in that room. She accommodated our request and for all 4 nights we were alone enjoying the privacy.  

Nights were still cold so I asked at reception for extra blankets. To my surprise, I was given robust electric plug in heater that made our room very comfortable for the whole night.

 Budget restaurant is just across the street. It offers all-day breakfast and great tasting meals, for a very friendly price (2 substantial meals for 10)

 Tesco expres is just around the corner. Also subway stations are few minutes walk. Generator also rents it's own bicycles for 10 a day.
Room Type: Bed in 4 Bed Dorm - Shared Bathrooms

Negative Reviews:
I'm here to report the worst experience I've ever had with accommodation.
The room advertised with photos on your app was far from reality. The room I was given had a window that wouldn't open, so there was literally no air circulation. It smelled of sweat because of this. On the first day, as it was raining in London, the room started to leak. The wooden locker they provided for clothes was on the floor and got soaked, making many of my clothes wet. When I went to the reception, they said they couldn't do anything because it was a structural problem and they were fully booked, so there was no other room available. They offered breakfast as compensation, even though I lost half of my suitcase contents due to wet clothes. The breakfast was worth only 9 euros.
Since the room had no air circulation, they provided two plug-in fans, but there weren't enough outlets because people were using them to charge their phones (which is understandable). So, we couldn't use the fans, and the room was like a sauna where no one could sleep.
The staff: every time I went to the reception to complain about the water leakage or lack of air circulation, they said they couldn't do anything and could only offer free breakfast. One staff member even suggested we leave the door open (how can you leave the door open in a room with 10 people trying to sleep and with constant movement?). It seems the Generator thinks a 9-euro breakfast compensates for a 150-euro room that isn't fit to host anyone. especially for the rude staff and disrespect. When addressing these issues at the reception, they even threatened to kick me out without giving me a chance to retrieve my belongings.
Room Type: Bed in 10 + Mixed Dormitory Room

Negative Reviews: sorry, no time to write, flight leaving soon....
Positive Reviews:
I did not do adequate research beforehand*, whereas I would have learned that guests are forbidden (!) to bring food from outside into the hostel, and there is no guests' kitchen.
  [  * I partly blame Booking.com for this because the format of the information provided for the hostel info appeared not to be following the format of the hostel profiles I've been used to, where the intended guest was lead to proceed through the relevant info that would have made clear the nature of the joint it is, as regards the facilities I wish to enjoy from a 'real' hostel, of which having at least a basic guests'-kitchen is one of those foundations.  ]
  I had only flown into London Heathrow, travelling lightweight, on a "visa-trip", to acquire fresh passport stamps, to document my departure from and then return to, Germany, in order to continue my current stay in Germany, (very much extended thanks to Covid to over two years), for a further three months period.
  I was not impressed by the sort of prices being asked for of hostellers intending to visit London, and the word "money-grabbers" springs to mind.
  Anyway, I had paid for what was thankfully only the first, of the intended two nights I'd planned to stay in London before the next cheap flight to return me to Germany. Before considering to pay Generator any more, I did not 'check in', but instead I went out to look for a more suitable cheap place to stay, and I ended up at a suitably priced bargain place I had stayed on previous visits. 
  I am disappointed that "The Generator", (the generator of greedy-wealth no doubt), seems to have got away with keeping my payment for having provided me with NOTHING. They failed to be a satisfactory and/or cheap, accommodation. 
I LIKE that I had NOT paid them for a second night.

Review Title: Generator London made me homeless in London
Negative Reviews: Well I didn't like that there is a cobbled stone road leading to the Generator entrance. I mean a lot of customers will have luggage in tow when they come to the Generator and they would have to drag their lugguage over the cobbled stone road which is far from ideal!
Positive Reviews:
Actually with this booking, I was to have my girlfriend join me in for a night and I was booked in for a week at Generator. That never happened because my own booking became something out a horror movie. I turned up to check in and I had the front desk person looking at me as if I had poop on my head.
Next thing I am being handed a card to say I MUST write down my email address. I was far from impressed with the manners of this reception person and the request that I write down my email didn't help.

I said I had already provided my email to booking dot com and how come they couldn't get my email from booking dot come.


Next thing the reception says I cannot stay at Generator for my one week booking if I do not give them my email address.

Apparently my driving licence ID was irrelevant and my email address was the most important requirement for check-in.

I turned to the second chap at the reception to intervene. And that fellow goes "nothing wrong has been done" and the first chap was right to treat the way he has.

At which I lost it. I said to the second fellow, "you are worse than he is". And next thing this second fellow is saying he knew I was trouble the moment I walked in and that he will check me out. So I said "check me out" and the second fellow who said he is the manager goes on to tell the first guy to cancel my booking and check me out.

And do we know what time it was?

Well this was almost midnight!

I turned out on the streets of London to be homeless after paying for a week's stay at the Generator, simply because I had objected to the manners-from-hell of our 2 Generator reception people on Wednesday!
